Creamed Kale
  --Cook's Country

1 1/2 lb curly kale, washed, stemmed, leaves cut into 2" pieces
1/2 tsp salt + more for water (2 tbsp)
1 tbsp vegetable oil
1 shallot, sliced thin
4 garlic cloves, sliced thin
1 1/2 c heavy cream
1/4 tsp pepper

Bring 4 qt water to boil in dutch oven over high heat. Add kale and 2 tbsp salt and cook until wilted, 2 min. Drain kale in colander, pressing with rubber spatula to remove excess water; set aside. Heat oil in now empty pot over medium heat until shimmering. Add shallot and garlic and cook until just softened, ~2 min. Stir in kale and cook until any remaining water has evaporated, 2 min. Add cream and pepper and cook until cream is thickened and clings to kale, ~3 min. Remove pot from and heat and cover to keep warm until ready to serve.
